2022-01-19 23:48:22	Atque	Hey. If I have a continuous positive pressure fan and it blows air from my house to outside. What do you guys reckon is best for removing humidity? Should the fan be up high or down low? I don't get how the water moves in the air. : (
2022-01-19 23:49:32	Bakunin	warmer air holds more moisture
2022-01-19 23:50:40	Bakunin	https://www.engineersedge.com/hvac-systems/images/psychrometric.gif
2022-01-19 23:50:44	<--	aruns (~aruns@176.27.177.204) has quit (Quit: leaving)
2022-01-20 00:14:15	PlanckWalk	Ifit's blowing air out of the house, wouldn't that make it a negative pressure fan?
2022-01-20 00:16:10	Bakunin	shh
2022-01-20 00:20:16	PlanckWalk	In general if you blow air out of the house, it will be replaced by air from the outside with whatever water vapour content that has.
2022-01-20 00:21:19	PlanckWalk	The most effective way to remove water vapour is with a dehumidifier
